				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Hotkeys to switch out what you're holding<a name="10162"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 14 03 1:53 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Yep, all those responses are correct... however, what I do is something like this:
<br />

<br />
When swarming, I nearly always have an instrument on my mouse pointer, either my drum or flute.  When I need to charm, or invis, I simply click the secondary slot that has my drum in it, thereby swaping out the instruments.  If you use numbers to do song hotkeys, you can hit the number to cast a song and then move the mouse and swap out the instrument in the 3 seconds it takes to cast, thereby getting the benefit of the instrument.  About the only time I don't have an instrument on my pointer is when I'm targeting a new mob (F8 doesn't seem to work well for me so I manually target), or am chant kiting for any length of time.  
<br />

<br />
I know this isn't what you were looking for, but with the cool UIs allowing access to inventories and secondary slots, it makes swaping out instruments nearly macro-like.  Certainly a lot easier than before.
<br />

<br />
Hope that helps.
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
